No Humane Law or Authoritie, differs from our owne Nationall 
                  To the 5.
                Lawes and Magistracie, to be admitted amongst us;

No such Moderator, to have any temporall Dignity or Lordship 
                  To the 1.
                nor temporall Iurisdiction or command annexed to his place, Nor such ease and freedome of life allowed, as heretofore;

And such a Moderator, superintendent Overseer, or (if any doe fansie the name, though Names of things so much deprav'd are fit, upon reformation of the things to be changed with them) such a Bishop [
                  〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
               ] may consist with primitive example; being thus now (as then) an office onely of speciall trust, and charge and care, and ministration for many Churches, not of sole Rule and command over any;
